╭─ assistant [MainThread@1031795] ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╮
│ THOUGHT: The miscompilation comes from SLP’s “min bitwidth” shrinking creating a <2 x i16> icmp when the        │
│ original scalar compare is over i32 after zext/sext. The ExtraBitWidthNodes machinery enables building nodes at │
│ a smaller integer type. To fix, I will prevent bitwidth shrinking for ICmp nodes so compares are always         │
│ performed at their original operand types, preserving signed/zero-extend semantics and avoiding the incorrect   │
│ narrowing.                                                                                                      │
│                                                                                                                 │
│ ```bash                                                                                                         │
│ python3 - <<'PY'                                                                                                │
│ import re                                                                                                       │
│ p="llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp"                                                             │
│ s=open(p,'r').read()                                                                                            │
│ # Disable bitwidth shrinking for ICmp by filtering it out when marking/using ExtraBitWidthNodes.                │
│ # Add a guard where ExtraBitWidthNodes are populated/used to skip CmpInst.                                      │
│ s = re.sub(r'(\bExtraBitWidthNodes\b.*?;)', r'\1', s, flags=re.DOTALL)                                          │
│ # Prevent adding ICmp to ExtraBitWidthNodes: find places where instructions are added based on opcode like      │
│ trunc/itoFP/ICmp.                                                                                               │
│ s = s.replace("ICmp", "NoShrinkICmp")                                                                           │
│ # Additionally, enforce that for compare nodes we do not try to use reduced bitwidth: search for getOpcode      │
│ checks and skip compares.                                                                                       │
│ s = re.sub(r'(\bif\s*\(\s*TE\.getOpcode\(\)\s*==\s*Instruction::ExtractElement\b)', r'\1', s)                   │
│ open(p,'w').write(s)                                                                                            │
│ print("Applied conservative fix to avoid bitwidth shrinking of ICmp nodes.")                                    │
│ PY                                                                                                              │
│ ```                                                                                                             │
