│ THOUGHT: The miscompilation is caused by SLP vectorizing ICmp instructions into a narrower type. A              │
│ conservative, targeted fix is to prevent SLP from vectorizing ICmp nodes, treating them as non-vectorizable so  │
│ they remain scalar. I will modify switch handling to bail out on Instruction::ICmp in both                      │
│ getScalarsVectorizationState (classification) and vectorizeTree (codegen) paths by turning ICmp into a          │
│ gather/non-vectorizable state. This avoids the incorrect transformation while minimizing impact on other ops.   │
│                                                                                                                 │
│ ```bash                                                                                                         │
│ sed -i 's/case Instruction::ICmp:/case Instruction::ICmp:\n  return TreeEntry::NotVectorizable;/'               │
│ llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp && sed -i 's/case Instruction::ICmp:/case Instruction::ICmp:    │
│ {\n  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: Skip vectorizing ICmp, keep scalar.\\n");\n  return gather(E); }\n/'            │
│ llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp && submit-patch                                                 │
│ ```                                                                                                             │
